---
title: Rosemary Meatloaf with Green Beans and Mashed Potatoes
description: Spiked with rosemary, these mini meatloaves are what happens when an American classic takes a trip through an herb garden, emerging with tons of fragrance and flavor. Even the mashed potatoes on the side, rich with garlic, get in on the aromatic action. And because of their miniature size, these loaves are quick-cooking too (not to mention super-cute).
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/5b4f72b7ae08b525e7569a42-732783a2.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/italian-meatloaf-5b4f72b7ae08b525e7569a42-833ce15f.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/rosemary-meatloaf-5b4f72b7ae08b525e7569a42
author: HelloFresh
nutrition:
  calories: 660 kcal
  fat: 35 g
  saturated fat: 15 g
  carbohydrates: 52 g
  sugar: 12 g
  protein: 34 g
  fiber: 8 g
  sodium: 430 mg
course: main course
cuisine: North America
servings: 2
time required: 40 minutes
---

Wash and dry all produce. Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to
400 degrees. Halve and peel @shallot{1}(peeled and halved), then mince until
you have ¼ cup. Mince @garlic{2%cloves}(minced). Strip and finely chop enough
@rosemary{¼%ounce}(finely chopped) leaves from stems to give you 1 tsp. Soak
@white bread{1%slice} with @chicken stock concentrate{1} and @milk{3%TBSP} in a
#medium bowl{}.

Break up soaked bread with hands until pasty. Add @ground beef{10%ounce},
half the chopped rosemary, half the garlic, minced shallot, @salt{}, and
@pepper{} (we used ½ tsp kosher salt). Mix until combined. Shape into two 1-inch
tall loaves and place on a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}. Bake in oven until
cooked through, about ~{25%minutes} (we'll check on them after ~{10%minutes}).

Meanwhile, cut @Yukon Gold potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch cubes. Place in a
#medium pot{} with a large pinch of salt. Add enough water to cover by 1 inch,
then bring to a boil. Cook until potatoes are easily pierced by a knife,
~{8-10%minutes}, then drain.

Toss @green beans{6%ounce} with a drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} and a pinch
of salt and pepper in another medium bowl. Once meatloaves have roasted
~{10%minutes}, add green beans to same baking sheet and continue baking until
green beans are tender and meatloaves are done, about ~{15%minutes}.

In pot used for potatoes, heat @butter{1%tablespoon}, remaining chopped
rosemary, and remaining garlic over low heat. Once garlic is fragrant, about
~{30%seconds} later, remove pot from heat and add potatoes and
@milk{⅓%cup}. Mash with a #potato masher{} or #fork{} until smooth. Season with
plenty of salt and pepper.

> TIP: Add more milk, if needed, to give potatoes a creamy consistency.

Divide mashed potatoes between #plates{}. Top with green beans and meatloaves
and serve.

> TIP: You can use the leftover rosemary sprigs as a decorative garnish.